<subSubSection id="C32272D2FFFCFFA0F6AAFBAC3EF2FB03" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFCFFA0F6AAFBAC3EF2FB03" blockId="6.[144,759,1077,1252]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F6AAFBAC3D54FBAA" box="[144,269,1077,1098]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name of the new genus comes from Greek 
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F6E7FBCA3D70FB88" box="[221,297,1107,1128]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Palaeo</emphasis>
(ancient), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFCFFA0F7EDFBCA3E5CFB88" authorityName="Smirnov &amp; Timms" authorityYear="1983" box="[471,517,1107,1128]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Rak" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F7EDFBCA3E5CFB88" box="[471,517,1107,1128]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Rak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the generic name of a chydorid with blunt rostrum and well-developed setae on the ventral margin of the valve, described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA95CA8FFFCFFA0F6AAFB363DE4FB25" author="Smirnov NN &amp; Timms BV" box="[144,445,1199,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref5715" refString="Smirnov NN, Timms BV. 1983. A revision of the Australian Cladocera (Crustacea). Records of the Australian Museum, Supplement 1: 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1983">Smirnov &amp; Timms (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFCFFA0F471FB363E20FB24" authorityName="Smirnov &amp; Timms" authorityYear="1983" box="[587,633,1199,1220]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Rak" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F471FB363E20FB24" box="[587,633,1199,1220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Rak</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Russian word (
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFCFFA0F794FB573D8FFB04" authorityName="Smirnov &amp; Timms" authorityYear="1983" box="[430,470,1230,1252]" class="Branchiopoda" genus="Rak" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diplostraca" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">rak</taxonomicName>
) for a crustacean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32272D2FFFCFFA0F6AAFA883D0FFA5F" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFCFFA0F6AAFA883D0FFA5F" blockId="6.[144,759,1296,1471]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F6AAFA883D5FFAC6" box="[144,262,1297,1318]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body moderately high, head capsule of ‘chydorid-type’ (compressed dorso-ventrally), covered with ‘flat’ head shield with rostrum truncated, valves with denticles and short setae along ventral margin of valves, mandible attached to point of joint of head shield and valve.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32272D2FFFCFFA0F6AAFA753E25F9C0" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFCFFA0F6AAFA753E25F9C0" blockId="6.[144,759,1516,1569]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F6AAFA753D57F9E1" box="[144,270,1516,1537]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Comments:</emphasis>
The genus is probably a few million years younger than 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFCFFA0F70FF9923D9AF9C0" authorityName="ROTUNDUS SMIRNOV" authorityYear="1992" box="[309,451,1547,1568]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" genus="Prochydorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F70FF9923D9AF9C0" box="[309,451,1547,1568]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Prochydorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C385ADAFFFCFFA0F43BF9923E2CF9C0" authorityName="MIRABILIS SMIRNOV" authorityYear="1992" box="[513,629,1547,1568]" class="Branchiopoda" family="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" genus="Archeoxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Branchiopoda (awaiting allocation)" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFCFFA0F43BF9923E2CF9C0" box="[513,629,1547,1568]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Archeoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
